      • getGeneratedIDBase

        public String getGeneratedIDBase()
        Description copied from class: FlexProject
        The base for compiler-generated id's on instance tags that need an id but don't have one specified in MXML. Compiler-generated ids for instance tags have the form #0, #1, etc. The old compiler generated an id of the form "_MyComponent_Button3", but we prefer short names that are the same in all classes, because these create smaller SWFs. Also, the compiler can be simpler and faster if it doesn't have to track how many instances of each type it has seen in a class. Rather than using some weird Unicode character, we've chosen # as a normal ASCII character that will look OK in the debugger but not conflict with any developer-specified id, since it isn't allowed in an ActionScript identifier or MXML id. It also can't conflict with any dynamic properties, because MXML classes are sealed.
        Overrides:
        getGeneratedIDBase in class FlexProject
